Enum Imt

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Imt>

    Serializable, Comparable<Imt>

    public enum Imt
extends Enum<Imt>
    Intesity measure type (Imt) identifiers. SA0P1 stands for spectal acceleration of 0.1 seconds.
    Author:
    Peter Powers

      • periods

        public static List<Double> periods(Collection<Imt> imts)
        Returns the List of periods for the supplied Imts. The result will be sorted according to the iteration order of the supplied Collection. Any non spectral acceleration Imts will have null values in the returned List.
        Parameters:
        imts - to list periods for
        Returns:
        a List of spectral periods
        See Also:
        saImts()

      • fromPeriod

        public static Imt fromPeriod(double period)
        Returns the spectral acceleration Imt associated with the supplied period. Due to potential floating point precision problems, this method internally checks values to within a small tolerance.
        Parameters:
        period - for Imt
        Returns:
        an Imt, or null if no Imt exsists for the supplied period

      • frequency

        public double frequency()
        Returns the frequency (in Hz) for this Imt. PGA returns 100 Hz, spectral periods return their expected value (1 / period), and PGV and PGD throw exceptions.
        Returns:
        the frequency associated with this Imt
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if called on PGV or PGD

      • isSA

        public boolean isSA()
        Returns true if this Imt is some flavor of spectral acceleration.
        Returns:
        true if this is a spectral period, false otherwise

      • saImts

        public static Set<Imt> saImts()
        Returns the Set of spectal acceleration IMTs.
        Returns:
        the IMTs that represent spectral accelerations

      • parseImt

        public static Imt parseImt(String s)
        Parses the supplied String into an Imt; method expects labels for specifically named intensity measure types ("PGA") and double value Strings for spectral periods ("0.2"). This method is not the same as valueOf(String).
        Parameters:
        s - String to parse
        Returns:
        an Imt, or null if supplied String is invalid
